main event: A report of four lights evolving in the window, observed for over an hour and a half.
interesting points: The objects were observed moving in a formation, initially going north and then changing direction to the south.
The objects were described as bright lights, with a consensus report on their direction of motion.
The report mentions that the duration of the observation was too long for a typical aircraft.
The report notes that maps did not indicate any known astronomical or satellite phenomena that could explain the sighting.
The analysis concludes that the case is classified as 'Unidentified' due to insufficient information and only a single witness without further qualifications.
sighted object: four lights evolving in the window
